Russian mercenary soldiers have been blitzed by Ukrainian forces in the battle for Soledar, footage has shown, as both sides continue their bloody battle over the Donetsk region in the east. Dozens of Russian Wagner Group soldiers, many of whom are on six-month releases from prison to fight in Ukraine, can be seen frantically hiding for cover in a rail yard as machine gun fire from nearby local forces rips through their defences. The Ukrainian outfit, likely to be the 24th Mechanised Brigade, which is holding out in Soledar, used a drone to scout the Russian positions and “wipe out” the small outfit. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...